Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,kæθə'lisiti]
*danh từ
 ■tính bao trùm, tính rộng khắp; tính phổ biến
 ■tính rộng lượng, tính rộng rãi, tính đại lượng
 ■đạo Thiên chúa, công giáo

sentences.en: 2) Example: ‘Comfort's catholicity of perception and image, strangely Whitmanesque in range, almost the exact opposite in aesthetic compulsion, continues to evoke that trembling atmospheric accumulative hinting at a cruel, an inexorably serene timelessness... Wrey Gardiner scores by aiming at simple bull's-eyes with precision. Only they are not so simple, and through this contented sadness runs more than the surface bitter-sweet of resignation’. (Poetry Quarterly.) [back]
sentences.vi: 2) Ví dụ: “Comfort’s catholicity of perception and image, strangely Whitmanesque in range, almost the exact opposite in aesthetic compulsion, continues to evoke that trembling atmospheric accumulative ginting at a cruel, an inexorably selene timelessness… Wrey Gardiner scores by aiming at simple bull’s-eyes with precision. Only they are not so simple, and through this contented sadness runs more than the surface bitter-sweet of resignation” (Poetry Quarterly.)
